      • onGaveUp

        public void onGaveUp(NodeReader reader)
        Description copied from interface: NodeReader.Listener
        Called when the NodeReader gave up reading the target znode.

        This callback is called when it detects one of the following when it tried to call a ZooKeeper's method (getData() or exists(). Note that this method may not be called so soon and may not be called at all.

        1. The given ZooKeeper instance reports AUTH_FAILED or CLOSED.
        2. This instance is marked as 'shouldFinish' by NodeReader.finish().
        Specified by:
        onGaveUp in interface NodeReader.Listener
        Parameters:
        reader - The NodeReader instance which this listener is associated with.
